==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Osmund
<hw>Os"mund</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
fern of the genus <gen>Osmunda</gen>, or flowering fern. The most
remarkable species is the <stype>osmund royal</stype>, or <stype>royal
fern</stype> (<spn>Osmunda regalis</spn>), which grows in wet or boggy
places, and has large bipinnate fronds, often with a panicle of capsules
at the top. The rootstock contains much starch, and has been used in
stiffening linen.</def><-- used as a substrate for growing orchids
-->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Osnaburg</ent>⟦br⟧
